On the other hand, they were confronted with screams of more aroused kittens, which were additionally lifted up.
The researchers consider their results to be meaningful despite the small sample.
"All females, even those who did not yet have their own offspring, reacted differentiatedly to the screams," Konerding said.
They turned to the speaker faster when this call of the very more aroused kittens played.
This ability may be innate or develop with sexual maturity.
